M||tx|---
M||name|receiving-code-rv
M||desc|>-
M||tx|Use when receiving code rv feedback, before implementing suggestions, esp if feedback seems unclear or technically questionable - requires tc rigor and verification, not performative agreement or blind implementation
M||vers|1.0.0
M||plat|[]
M||meta|
M||herm|
M||tags|[dv, nx, ts, architecture, vc, ap-rt, bd, productivity]
M||tx|---
M|Over|tx|Code rv requires tc evaluation, not emotional perf.
M|Over|**Co|** Verify before implementing. Ask before assuming. tc correctness over sl comfort.
M|The |tx|```
M|The |WHEN|
M|The |1. R|Complete feedback w/o reacting
M|The |2. U|Restate requirement in own words (or ask)
M|The |3. V|Check against codebase reality
M|The |4. E|Technically sound for THIS codebase?
M|The |5. R|tc acknowledgment or reasoned pushback
M|The |6. I|One item at a time, tst each
M|The |tx|```
M|Forb|**NE|**
M|Forb|it|"You're absolutely right!" (explicit CLAUDE.md violation)
M|Forb|it|"Great point!" / "Excellent feedback!" (performative)
M|Forb|it|"Let me im that now" (before verification)
M|Forb|**IN|**
M|Forb|it|Restate the tc requirement
M|Forb|it|Ask clarifying questions
M|Forb|it|Push back w/ tc reasoning if wrong
M|Forb|it|Just start working (actions > words)
M|Hand|tx|```
M|Hand|IF a|
M|Hand|tx|STOP - do not im anything yet
M|Hand|tx|ASK for clarification on unclear items
M|Hand|WHY|Items may be related. Partial understanding = wrong implementation.
M|Hand|tx|```
M|Hand|**Ex|**
M|Hand|tx|```
M|Hand|your|"Fix 1-6"
M|Hand|tx|You understand 1,2,3,6. Unclear on 4,5.
M|Hand|ÔŁî WR|im 1,2,3,6 now, ask abt 4,5 later
M|Hand|Ôťů RI|"I understand items 1,2,3,6. Need clarification on 4 and 5 before proceeding."
M|Hand|tx|```
M|From|it|**Trusted** - im after understanding
M|From|it|**Still ask** if scope unclear
M|From|it|**No performative agreement**
M|From|it|**Skip to action** or tc acknowledgment
M|From|tx|```
M|From|BEFO|
M|From|1. C|Technically correct for THIS codebase?
M|From|2. C|Breaks existing functionality?
M|From|3. C|Reason for current implementation?
M|From|4. C|Works on all platforms/versions?
M|From|5. C|Does reviewer understand full context?
M|From|IF s|
M|From|tx|Push back w/ tc reasoning
M|From|IF c|
M|From|Say |"I can't verify this w/o [X]. shd I [investigate/ask/proceed]?"
M|From|IF c|
M|From|tx|Stop and discuss w/ your human partner first
M|From|tx|```
M|From|**yo|** "External feedback - be skeptical, but check carefully"
M|YAGN|tx|```
M|YAGN|IF r|
M|YAGN|tx|grep codebase for actual usage
M|YAGN|IF u|"This endpoint isn't called. Remove it (YAGNI)?"
M|YAGN|IF u|Then im properly
M|YAGN|tx|```
M|YAGN|**yo|** "You and reviewer both rp to me. If we don't need this feature, don't add it."
M|Impl|tx|```
M|Impl|FOR |
M|Impl|tx|1. Clarify anything unclear FIRST
M|Impl|2. T|
M|Impl|it|Blocking issues (breaks, sec)
M|Impl|it|Simple fixes (typos, imports)
M|Impl|it|Complex fixes (refactoring, logic)
M|Impl|tx|3. tst each fix individually
M|Impl|tx|4. Verify no regressions
M|Impl|tx|```
M|When|Push|
M|When|it|Suggestion breaks existing functionality
M|When|it|Reviewer lacks full context
M|When|it|Violates YAGNI (unused feature)
M|When|it|Technically incorrect for this stack
M|When|it|Legacy/compatibility reasons exist
M|When|it|Conflicts w/ your human partner's architectural decisions
M|When|**Ho|**
M|When|it|Use tc reasoning, not defensiveness
M|When|it|Ask specific questions
M|When|it|Reference working tests/code
M|When|it|Involve your human partner if architectural
M|When|**Si|** "Strange things are afoot at the Circle K"
M|Ackn|When|
M|Ackn|tx|```
